&nbsp;
"The formula invented by Confindustria" High Adriatic, precise, "is effective for training young people here and training in the industries of our North East. The young people will then be able to decide whether to continue in Italy or return here, is a happy formula, I thank the president of Confindustria Orsini who has taken this formula because&nbsp; be repeated in other areas of Italy". "They are initiatives that are located in the broadest context of friendship between Ghana and Italy. Yesterday, in talks with the President of Ghana we recorded on every topic a sharing of visions and a common will to strengthen the bond - he concludes -. Here we breathe the spirit of collaboration between Ghana and Italy, our future is common and is entrusted to young people. Here is an exemplary model that I hope will be repeated on other occasions and in other realities."
&nbsp;
"The project represents the contribution we make to the Mattei> plan", explains, for its part, Michelangelo Agrusti of Confindustria Alto Adriatico. "It uses what is foreseen by the Cutro decree, which establishes, if planned, the legal migration quotas. All these boys who will come to us, in manufacturing but also in the tertiary," he adds. Before returning to Italy, Mattarella then visited the ship Bettica, patrolman of the fourth division of the Navy that began on March 25 the activity of surveillance in the Gulf of Guinea, in the context of the operation 'Gabinia', aimed at contrasting the phenomenon of piracy. On board the ship, the president is updated on the activities and assists the simulation of an operation.&nbsp; The Gabinia mission in which the ship is engaged, says, "is of great importance and can take place also for the hospitality that the government of Ghana guarantees in the port of Tema".
&nbsp;
"The mission", he adds, "has a great and primary purpose for cohabitation in the world and for freedom of navigation through the contrast to piracy, illicit trafficking and the exercise of naval diplomacy". "I wish to extend greetings to all crews and personnel on the ground. And I address a message of greeting to Vespucci ship yesterday passed from the Pacific Ocean to the Atlantic dubbing Cape Horn, an event of great importance for a sailor, made with great mastery to demonstrate the great ability of ship Vespucci and our Navy," he concludes, thanking the crew for the constant commitment. The visit to the Bettica ship marks the last stage of the African mission, which led Mattarella on an official three-day visit to Ivory Coast, and then to Ghana. The return of the head of state is scheduled in the evening in Rome.

