&nbsp; But from the other allies on the left, appeals to the unity. "A common element of decision would have been necessary" in the choice to stop the primary for the leader of Si and MP of Avs Nicola Fratoianni. "Now from such a situation you can leave in the only possible way, stubbornly looking for a unitary solution - he adds - to win the elections in Bari serve alliances. So, where there are difficulties, there is a need for union candidates to agree and indicate a unitary solution. There's no other way. You work this way. The point is not the wide, narrow, just or not right field. The point is to build an alternative model to the dexts, there is the possibility to do so and we must stubbornly work in this direction".
More clearly with&nbsp;Conte is Angelo Bonelli, other voice of Avs: "Interrupting the primary in Bari was an incomprehensible fact and harm to the city. Yesterday Vito Leccese gave his willingness to take a step back to make three forwards. Now it is up to Laforgia to take this step back, we wait for him" "Welcome to the planet Earth, nation Italy, dear Elly&nbsp;Schlein. Did it take the slap of Bari, to wake Nazareno from ideological fascinations in Thai sauce? - says Enrico Borghi, group leader in the Senate of Italia Viva - che&nbsp;Conte&nbsp;aiutasse the right we had already seen. Now, however, in politics it is necessary to be consequent: and to draw the conclusion that the entire political line of the so-called 'wide field' is failing, and useful only to allow the right easy yield victories. Because otherwise, dear Elly, you do not make politics, but situationism." "In Bari it seemed that the centerpiece had instrumentalized the situation, but in the end the judiciary went on revealing further scandals. The real political attack came from&nbsp;Conte&nbsp; which broke the alliance of center-left. For us this is a favorable situation but we are serious people and we feel to give a true alternative in a region like Puglia where the centerleft is rooted. Winning will not be easy but it is possible to give a serious answer", confirms to Omnibus the deputy and national manager of the departments of Forza Italia, Alessandro Cattaneo. "I hope that after years and years of left with Decaro and Emiliano, the center, I hope to guide Lega and with a candidacy of the League, also won in Bari. But not for the investigations, not for the shooting, not for the mafia families, not for the exchange vote. On that, I let the judges and journalists work," says Carroccio Matteo&nbsp;Salvini.&nbsp.

